sql:
SELECT institution_name 
FROM institutions 
WHERE total_capacity = (
    SELECT MAX(total_capacity) 
    FROM institutions
);

external_knowledge:
- "Opening their doors" metaphorically refers to offering seats in courses;
- "More than fifty percent of their total capacity" means the intake is greater than half of the total capacity;
- "Benchmark of a hundred seats" refers to the intake having to exceed 100 seats.

- Admitted lots of times refers to having been accepted into an institution 10 or more times;
- The types of quotas include categories like All Indian Quota and Home State Quota;
- The query focuses on successful admissions, which are applications with a decision status of 'accepted'.

- 'hopefuls' refers to the applicants;
- 'targeting the Computer Science program' means applying for the B.Tech in Computer Science quota;
- 'university in Assam' refers to Assam University, Silchar, Assam.
